At the heart of the new cap epidemic, the much busier couriers rarely see each other on the street, meeting couriers from other companies who don't know their names, but who come to the rescue and bond at Special Times

By Yu Qin, CAIJING correspondent

Editor | Lu Wei

After the epidemic of new crown pneumonia spread in Wuhan, the whole city began to be sensitive to body temperature. From time to time, people shouted to Shang Liming at the side of streets and streets and at the community entrance: "Come, take your temperature! " Shang Liming was a courier, jD.com Logistics Wuhan Baofeng Business Department, its distribution in the central region of the epidemic, including the Wuhan Union Hospital, Wuhan Lung Hospital.

As of February 10,18,454 new cases of pneumonia had been confirmed in Wuhan, a city with a population of more than 10 million.

Dawn was not so much afraid of the job at the heart of the city as of passing the virus on to his family. "One can carry it on one's own if one is unlucky enough to catch it. " By February 5, danger suddenly "became visible" before his eyes. It is an open old community, each building new marked "epidemic building" or "non-epidemic building" , yellow bottom black word, a sudden entrance stairs. The building is very short, climb up"there is epidemic building", still dawn dare not as usual pant,"a person comes down, you do not know he is not calorific

Since 10:00 on January 23, Wuhan, known as the thoroughfare of nine provinces, announced the suspension of ferry and long-distance passenger transport, the temporary closure of airports, railway stations and other departure channels, to prevent the spread of the new pneumonia. These rare major measures, by the outside world known as the "City" anti-epidemic. In the city, the public transportation, the subway stops running, the community implements the close type management.

Logistics has become an indispensable dependence in Wuhan city. Hospitals are sending out signals that supplies are in short supply; residents of the isolated city of Wuhan are ordering Rice, oil and salt from the Internet; and large quantities of supplies are pouring into Wuhan and being distributed to various logistics sites.

Like Shang Liming, courier Luo Zongping's distribution area is also in the central region of the epidemic, where he is the Danbird Logistics Wuhan Huaqiao Station, only about 1 km from the south China Seafood Market.

Located in Jianghan District, Wuhan, the South China Seafood Market was once the largest wholesale seafood market in central China. In addition to seafood, the market is also known for its "game" such as rabbits, pheasants and snakes. An epidemic has brought the market to an abrupt end. At the end of 2019, there were many cases of pneumonia in Wuhan, most of which were related to the south China Seafood Market. After that, the relevant departments decided to close the South China Wholesale Seafood Market, for Environmental Health Control.

Luo Zongping in the delivery of express, sometimes still receive the address written south China Seafood Market, he had to call to ask for a new address. Write down a string of new addresses, as to the addressee, whether the south China Seafood Market had done business, is to sell fruit or wildlife, Luo zongping did not dare to think. He said he was still afraid when he cycled past the closed south China seafood market.

Shang Liming and Rochom told Caijing on average that the volume of orders for this year's Spring Festival has surged, at least doubling from the same period last year. Due to the shortage of staff, the grass-roots management back to line delivery.

The streets are deserted. Most of the people you meet on the way are sanitation workers, police officers, community workers, food delivery workers, or other couriers. In the same delivery area, couriers from both companies met as if they were old friends. "Hey, you're out, too! " One says, while the other quips, "you're out in the middle of all this? "

They can't name each other. They bond at special moments.

Unit volume rose sharply, grass-roots managers also on the line

"This outbreak really feels like big data is playing a very important role in the middle, " Si SI, head of central China marketing at JD.com logistics, told Caijing, jd.com will use the data to forecast future orders. Back in the early days of the epidemic, JD.com observed from behind-the-scenes data that orders for masks, disinfectants and even white vinegar and vitamin C had started to rise, prompting them to stock up and mobilize resources.

The data tells us much more than that. He says the entire supply chain is interconnected, and Jd.com can see problems in the data and hear voices on the front lines to make decisions based on the overall data. For example, how many vehicles and personnel can be stored in order to meet these consumer orders; after the closure of some cities, medical supplies can be delivered, but people's livelihood supplies may not necessarily be delivered. In this case, you need to be aware of which products are likely to run out of time before you decide whether to adjust production upstream; if something goes wrong at the end, the warehouse can react with big data and stop production immediately or intelligently deploy production capacity, there will not be all the goods to the site or stacked in the high-speed port of the situation.

During the outbreak, JD.com logistics was co-ordinated by groups, regional companies were deployed on the front lines and regional companies were able to make effective decisions because they were supported by big data, says Si.

In addition to the power of science and technology, people are an important part of logistics. People in the logistics industry said that no matter how powerful high-tech and big data are, a complete logistics industry still needs the most ordinary and traditional people to stick to it, including offline rescue platforms and supply platforms, and logistics workers who overcome their fears.

Luo Zongping, the Wuhan Huaqiao station chief of Danbird Logistics, is one of 12 workers in Huaqiao Station with an average daily delivery of about 1,000 pieces. Usually during the new year, orders to fall by half, only half the staff stay. Affected by the epidemic, the single amount of dry humped up, but half of the staff has gone home for the New Year, stay down the staff, than usual to do double the work.

Danniao logistics is the distribution company under the CAINIAO Network, responsible for TMALL supermarket distribution. Arrived at the logistics site, the last express station in the cat super warehouse. Responsible for the Warehouse Cat Ultra Warehouse, and the end of the logistics site face the same pressure. Rookie Wuhan Cat Super Warehouse Head Yan Pei told the "financial" reporter, during the epidemic, the unit volume increased one or two times, the staff's daily working hours increased from 8 hours to 12 hours. During the Spring Festival, Yan Pei at home in Wuhan, in order to get back to the unit as soon as possible to support colleagues, she tried to drive a lot of routes to go through.

On the third day of the Lunar New Year, Dan-bird Logistics Qiao Station Master Jing Fengling returned from his hometown in Henan to support colleagues in Wuhan. Due to the "closure of the village" , the road in her hometown was blocked by mud, stones and tree trunks. She had to find an excavator to open the way before she was able to get out from her hometown. On the highway, traffic police reminded her, "now into Wuhan will not go out. " She explained that she is responsible for distribution, to ensure that Wuhan residents online shopping for living materials can be delivered, must enter Wuhan, and finally be released.

Shang Liming is station master assistant, his logistics point is slightly larger, the daily delivery volume of about 2500 pieces, the normal configuration is station Master 1, Station Master Assistant 2,21. By the time the city was sealed off, 16 employees had gone home for the Lunar New Year.

Single volume up, the two stations are busy into a gyroscope, the grass-roots managers have not sent pieces on the line, on the other side, anxious to call staff back to work. But at this time, even if the staff have the intention to come back is also difficult, "even if the village, also can not enter the city. ".

Luo Zongping said that the staff who went home for the New Year, as far as Xinjiang, were being separated at home because they were returning from Wuhan. The most recent, who lives in the Huangpi District District of Wuhan, had a typical one hour commute, but now buses are stopped and it is difficult to get around. Most people come from other parts of Hubei, and at this time, outside Wuhan, most cities in Hubei are also in the "closed city" state, want to return to Wuhan from home, it can be said that many barriers.

During the Spring Festival, Rookie Wuhan Cat Super Warehouse 150 people left behind, recent employees often worry, when they can go home. Therefore, for the grass-roots managers, how to placate on-the-job employees has become an important task.

Yan Pei said that under the situation of "closing the city" in Wuhan, the employees could not leave Wuhan. Beginning on January 22, Rookie Wuhan Maochaocang has provided all front-line employees with protective materials, including medical masks and sulfur soap. All warehouses, distribution centers and stations are regularly disinfected every day, the most stringent preventive measures are implemented, and the health of staff, especially front-line distributors, is monitored multiple times a day, "Make employees feel safer working in a warehouse than at home. ". At the same time, the company has also purchased Special Covid-19 insurance for its employees, providing them with increased benefits from food, clothing, housing, transportation and other aspects, and encouraging them psychologically. The Human Resources Department will give an answer to any employee's request.

Luo's site also takes the precaution to a state of the art -- More than three temperature readings a day -- and ships them out with goggles, gloves, and surgical masks, and, on the advice of Concorde's doctors, keeps them mostly separate from their families.

Besides the mask, the rice flour oil and salt orders are the most

On the one hand, it's a quantum leap, and on the other hand, it's an impassable community door.

Normally, couriers can go into the neighborhood and knock on the recipient's door. Even if no one is home, most people will agree to leave the delivery at the door. But during the outbreak, the community has taken a closed management, couriers can not enter the community, the guard is not willing to accept the courier, so only in the community at the door to complete the handover. The process can be extremely lengthy.

"sometimes a call to wait 20 minutes, if a pile of goods, to deliver 20 to 30 people how to do? " Shang Liming said, the delivery can not into the district led to inefficient delivery, every day the site has express storage.

Luo zongping afraid to large-scale community delivery, large area, from the corner of the building to the door, it takes a lot of time, plus the inside of the road around, out of the building, out of the community also have to go through the checkpoint, is to let him wait. Once, he went to the Wansongyuan residential area in Wuhan delivery, not to the community, called ahead, let the recipient ready to go downstairs, but wait for him to the community door, have not seen people. He repeatedly called several times, "every customer said, soon soon" , but Luo zongping finally waited for nearly an hour, before the recipient appeared at the gate.

"At first glance, the ban on couriers is intended to be more effective in preventing epidemic diseases, but it is likely to lead to the opposite of prevention and control, " he said at a State Council joint prevention and Control Mechanism press conference on Feb. 6, hou Yanbo, Deputy Director of the State Post Bureau, said that the risk of transmission through mail is extremely low, and from the point of view of epidemic prevention and control, in response to the issue of "the community does not allow couriers to enter, which affects delivery speed. " It would be better to let couriers in, rather than keep them out and let the residents go downstairs to get it themselves. He also urges that neighborhoods with smart boxes open the door for delivery boys, and that neighborhoods without smart boxes be set aside for mail and delivery.

Usually during the Chinese new year, nuts class list more, this year the sudden change in painting style. In addition to face masks, consumers in Wuhan are more likely to hoard grain. Luo zongping handled express, mostly rice oil and salt. One day, he sent a courier, the phone late nobody answered, until 8 pm, dark, the customer did not call back. That is an old couple, Luo zongping said to them, it is already off duty now, and again to send to tomorrow. The old man explained that the family is running out of food, during the outbreak did not dare to go out, specifically let his son buy Rice on the Internet. Luo zongping found that express, it is a bag of rice. He suddenly realized that what he had done was to solve the problem of food and clothing for others.

The Mask is another item that needs to be. Luo Zongping to "finance and economics" reporter mentioned a recent case that made him "laugh and cry" : The client is a girl in her 20s, received Luo zongping delivery call thousands of thanks: "Very, very grateful, I thought I did not receive! " But at this time, luo Zongping was blocked from entering the residential area, and the girl could not walk down the stairs as she had to wear a mask, but she did not even have a mask, and the delivery was just a box of masks.

Luo Zongping said a lot of Nice things to the security guard, took his temperature, filled in the registration form, sprayed disinfection water, and finally entered the community. The client opened the package, took out two masks and sent them to Luo Zongping, which made him happy for a long time.

Occasionally, something made Luo zongping angry. Once, the order is two boxes of water, delivery place is a few hundred meters away from the south China Seafood Market community, customers do not want to come down to take, security and Luo Zongping. The customer attitude is tough, in the telephone said: "You do not deliver on the complaint. " The goods did not deliver, Luo zongping received the customer's three complaints. Later security told Luo Zongping, his delivery customers have long been infected, so can not come out. Luo zongping was still frightened.

"This is the only thing that happened to tens of thousands of packages throughout the Chinese New Year, " Luo said, adding that most of his customers were friendly to him, and some sent him messages saying, "thank you very much. Take care of yourself. ".

During the outbreak, many goods were not available offline, and people found that they could still buy them online, he said. Even if there were delays in some areas, it would be easier for consumers to get their goods to him, it's more than people expected. Therefore, has received many from the consumer's praise. JD.com used to target its workers as being efficient and time-sensitive, but during the epidemic it did not apply as much scrutiny to deliverymen because the delivery boys were the "retrograde ones" fighting on the front lines.

Delivery to concord, "Four or five times a day. "

One day, just before the Spring Festival, Luo noticed a strange delivery. The address of the delivery was Wuhan Union Hospital, but the name and telephone number of the recipient were not written down. He is very confused, dial the sender's phone, the other side let him directly to the hospital, "randomly find a doctor nurse. ". Luo zongping did, but the nurse was startled, busy to him: "I do not accept things, do not accept things. " After this, sent to the hospital materials, suddenly more. Luo zongping this just thought, before the original that did not have the recipient's express delivery, is in fact the netizen donates the material.

Because medical supplies and medicines are hard to buy on the market and in short supply, many medical staff have to find their own way to buy. Since January 23, the Hubei Provincial Hospital of traditional Chinese Medicine, the Wuhan Union Hospital, the People's Hospital of Wuhan University, the Zhongnan Hospital of Wuhan University, the Third Hospital of Wuhan City, and other hospitals have issued public announcements, solicit donations of medical supplies from all walks of life.

According to Luo Zongping, since the "closure of the city, " hundreds of items of caring materials sent to the Union Medical College Hospital can be received every day at the station. At most, there are more than 200 items, sometimes from the station to the hospital, and sometimes from the hospital to send a car to receive them, at the earliest, a car arrived just after 5 a.m. , and the doctor was especially happy to see the yellow label on the package because it was protective.

There are a lot of new pneumonia patients in Concorde Hospital. Patients usually come and go through gate 1, Gate 4 is near the family area, and a few patients come and go. Luo zongping usually unloading is in door 3, door 4, occasionally can meet patients, "a see wearing striped clothes, immediately stand far. "

Every morning at 7:00 a.m. , the sorting center's Train arrives at the station, where it waits for unloading at dawn. During the outbreak, the amount of materials sent to concord is particularly large, if the site of the car delivery, "At least four or five to drag. ". The mail boxes were filled with messages such as "Angel in White" , "any medical staff" , "doorman to doctor to nurse" , "please send this to these lovely people by Courier" .., for the first time he saw the words on these delivery forms, he was heartened and shocked.

According to the CAIJING reporter, the JD.com Logistics Epidemic Material Special Action Team assumes the responsibility of internal and external material co-ordination, but in Wuhan and other cities where the epidemic is more prominent, the front has a lot of decision-making and contingency rights.

After application, in Wuhan, Jingdong agreed to send the goods directly to the Union Hospital by car from the sorting center. On his first delivery to Concord Hospital, the driver arrived at Gate 4 of the hospital and refused to drive in again, 500 meters away from the donation center. "It's human nature to seek good luck and avoid evil, I can understand that, " said Shang Liming, finally he got out of the car and used the trailer to pull back and forth three or four times.

CAINIAO network-related sources, Wuhan "closed city" on the third day, Cainiao United Nations more than 30 logistics companies to open free transport of relief supplies in Wuhan Green Channel. After 24-hour 400 hotline is used to collect the donation demand of the whole country and the whole world, the smart supply chain background of Cainiao combines the local road conditions and transportation resources to realtime and dynamically allocate the transportation capacity. As of February 10, relief supplies from 30 countries and regions have been sent or are being sent to China, with nearly 14 million masks received from South Korea alone.

Jd.com logistics began providing emergency drug shipments to local drug companies on January 21, and announced on January 22 that it would begin priority distribution of designated orders from medical institutions, january 25 officially opened throughout the country to ride to assist Wuhan Relief Supplies Compulsory Transport Channel. As of February 6, JD.com logistics has sent more than 1,600 tons of epidemic prevention and relief materials and emergency supplies to Wuhan and surrounding areas through intelligent dynamic deployment, coordinated warehousing, transportation and distribution.

Even before the outbreak, dawn had seen the South Korean film "Flu. ". The film tells the story of the spread of the deadly swine flu virus in the city. Similar to reality, the city is closed in the movie.

Shang Liming said that when he saw the film, he had a sense of helplessness, that people are really very ordinary, very ordinary. Unlike the despair of watching a play, when the movie actually happens, "At least I can do something small. "
